com.mojang.datafixers.optics

Class Procompose<F extends K2,G extends K2,A,B,C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mojang.datafixers.optics.Procompose<F,G,A,B,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    F - The witness type of the first transformation.
    G - The witness type of the second transformation.
    A - The input type.
    B - The output type.
    C - The intermediate type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Procompose<F<A,?C>,G<?C,B>>

    public final class Procompose<F extends K2,G extends K2,A,B,C>
extends Object
    A composition of profunctors. Where a profunctor represents a transformation from one type to another, a Procompose represents the composition of these transformations. This is analogous to function composition, but for a general profunctor.

    A Procompose<F, G, A, B, C> is analogous to a transformation F from A to C followed by a transformation G from C to B.

    Type Shape:
    %.Type.[%(0,2,4),%(1,4,3)]
    See Also:
    Profunctor, Function.compose(Function)
